WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.920
So this is the second part in a two-part webinar. The first one was a few weeks

00:00:05.920 --> 00:00:10.560
ago with RStudio Server Pro and then this one is about ShinyServer Pro. These

00:00:10.560 --> 00:00:13.360
webinars are slightly different than some of the other webinars that we've

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:20.440
done in that they're geared towards administration of our products and they

00:00:20.440 --> 00:00:28.360
are, you know, we'll be referring to the admin guides frequently. So this one's

00:00:28.360 --> 00:00:32.040
about ShinyServer Pro and I'm really excited to do it and I've got a lot to

00:00:32.040 --> 00:00:38.200
go through so we should just get started. To give you a brief background of our

00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:43.639
product stack, for those of you that are maybe not that familiar with RStudio

00:00:43.639 --> 00:00:47.200
products, we have an IDE, we have this thing called Shiny which is what we're

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:51.599
talking about today, and then we develop all these open source packages that are

00:00:51.599 --> 00:00:57.919
freely available to the community. What is Shiny? Shiny is a web application

00:00:57.919 --> 00:01:01.000
framework for R. You can turn your analyses into interactive web

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:05.839
applications and you don't need to know HTML, CSS, or JavaScript in order to build

00:01:05.839 --> 00:01:13.959
these. This is a Hello World script that's on our main page, shiny.rstudio.com

00:01:13.959 --> 00:01:17.519
and you can see that you have some interactive controls and you can add

00:01:17.519 --> 00:01:22.279
some nice features here and then you can interact with this app. This app is built

00:01:22.279 --> 00:01:26.879
with two pieces, one is the UI script that defines the user interface and then

00:01:26.879 --> 00:01:33.320
the other one is server.r which defines the actual functionality of the app

00:01:33.320 --> 00:01:40.320
itself. For example, histogram is in here and as well, which is right here, as well

00:01:40.320 --> 00:01:44.639
as like the rug plot and the density lines. So this is a Shiny app, we have a

00:01:44.639 --> 00:01:47.360
lot of lectures and discussions about Shiny apps, we're not going to be really

00:01:47.360 --> 00:01:50.360
talking about developing Shiny apps today, we're going to be talking about

00:01:50.480 --> 00:01:57.000
hosting those Shiny apps using Shiny Server Pro. The other thing that's a

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:00.599
little bit different about these webinars than the previous ones that we

00:02:00.599 --> 00:02:04.639
have done is that these really are focused on our professional products and

00:02:04.639 --> 00:02:08.199
we're doing that because if you're going to have an administrative team managing

00:02:08.199 --> 00:02:12.039
the products, you're probably going to be using our professional products. So a lot

00:02:12.039 --> 00:02:15.479
of the features that we'll be talking about today are specifically pro-related

00:02:15.479 --> 00:02:19.240
products and I'm not going to differentiate between pro and open

00:02:19.240 --> 00:02:23.880
source here, I'm going to, I will solely be referring to pro features without

00:02:23.880 --> 00:02:33.360
making that distinction. So every Shiny application requires a Shiny Server on

00:02:33.360 --> 00:02:39.520
the back end. Shiny Server Pro is the product that we use to help us secure

00:02:39.520 --> 00:02:44.600
performance and monitor resource utilization, you know, and really make

00:02:44.759 --> 00:02:49.880
your applications available to everyone in your organization or your

00:02:49.880 --> 00:02:54.320
enterprise. We oftentimes get the question, what is the difference between Shiny and

00:02:54.320 --> 00:02:58.839
Shiny Server? It's a really good question, I can relate because I had the same

00:02:58.839 --> 00:03:03.880
question when it first was being developed. Shiny is an open source package

00:03:03.880 --> 00:03:09.800
that is used to develop applications and it's used to build these responsive and

00:03:09.800 --> 00:03:16.199
powerful applications. Shiny Server Pro is professional software that you

00:03:16.199 --> 00:03:21.520
use to host the applications and it's designed to scale, protect, and manage and

00:03:21.520 --> 00:03:22.800
secure your environment.

